# .gitignore for papers/jss_2026
#
# Policy:
#   COMMITTED  - source (code, config, .tex, bib, JSS class files), the public
#                reproduction data inputs, the simulation reference outputs,
#                the paper figures the LaTeX build embeds, and the compiled PDF.
#   IGNORED    - regenerable run outputs, the replication bundle, and
#                LaTeX/Python build detritus.
#
# A reviewer can clone, run replicate.py, and reproduce every result. The
# inputs and the embedded figures are tracked so the paper compiles from a
# fresh clone without first running the pipeline.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LaTeX build detritus  (article.pdf is TRACKED — see below)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.lof
*.lot
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.nav
*.snm
*.vrb
build_test.*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python build / cache detritus
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Regenerable run outputs and the replication bundle
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Study outputs, regenerated by the simulation/application scripts.
simulations/results/
simulations/results_calibrated/
# The replication bundle is a build output of make_replication_zip.py.
factorlasso_jss_replication.zip

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Explicitly TRACKED despite living near generated content
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public reproduction data inputs (yfinance-built ETF panel + factor NAVs).
# These are NOT licensed and ARE committed so reproduction runs from a clone.
!applications/data/
!applications/data/etf_excess_logreturns.csv
!applications/data/futures_risk_factors.csv
!applications/data/riskfree_monthly.csv

# Paper figures the LaTeX build reads via \includegraphics (both .pdf and
# .png), plus the Table 2 artefacts emitted by analysis.py, tracked so the
# paper compiles from a fresh clone:
!paper/figures/
!paper/figures/*.pdf
!paper/figures/*.png
!paper/figures/*.csv
!paper/figures/*.tex

# The compiled paper PDF is shipped for reader/reviewer convenience.
# (Remove the '!' line to stop tracking it.)
!paper/article.pdf
